# Server Data Patterns

All database reads and writes follow a strict server-first architecture. Pair with [clerk-auth.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/clerk-auth.mdc) for auth and [drizzle-database.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/drizzle-database.mdc) for queries.

## Data retrieval — Server Components only

Fetch data in async Server Components (`app/**/page.tsx`, layouts, or server-only modules they import). Query Drizzle directly on the server.

```typescript
// app/decks/page.tsx
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { db } from "@/src/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/src/db/schema";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  const decks = await db
    .select()
    .from(decksTable)
    .where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}
```

Pass fetched data to Client Components as props. Client Components must not fetch or mutate database data.

## Mutations — Server Actions only

All `insert`, `update`, and `delete` operations go through Server Actions in files marked with `"use server"`. Co-locate actions under `app/**/actions.ts` or `src/actions/`.

```typescript
"use server";

import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/src/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/src/db/schema";
import { createDeckSchema, type CreateDeckInput } from "@/src/validations/decks";

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.parse(input);

  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  const [deck] = await db
    .insert(decksTable)
    .values({ userId, name: parsed.name })
    .returning();

  return deck;
}
```

## Validation — Zod required

Define Zod schemas in `src/validations/` (or next to the action). Export both the schema and an inferred TypeScript type.

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";

export const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().trim().min(1).max(100),
});

export type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;
```

Every Server Action must:

1. Accept a typed object parameter (`CreateDeckInput`, not `FormData`)
2. Validate with `schema.parse(input)` or `schema.safeParse(input)` before any database work
3. Return typed results or structured errors — never trust unvalidated client input

```typescript
// Client Component
import { createDeck, type CreateDeckInput } from "@/app/decks/actions";

async function onSubmit() {
  const input: CreateDeckInput = { name: deckName };
  await createDeck(input);
}
```

## Do not

- Fetch database data in Client Components (`useEffect` + `fetch`, React Query against internal APIs, etc.)
- Perform inserts, updates, or deletes outside Server Actions (Route Handlers, API routes, client-side Drizzle)
- Use `FormData` as a Server Action parameter type — parse form fields into a typed object, then validate with Zod
- Skip Zod validation or accept `unknown` / `any` action inputs
- Use Route Handlers for CRUD that belongs in Server Actions
